    {"p": "A + 被 (+ B) + verb", "e": "The 被 passive puts the thing acted on first; the doer comes after 被 and can be vague, like 人 'someone'. For example, 书被人借走了 means 'the book was borrowed by someone'.", "x": "那本书被人借走了。 — That book has been borrowed by someone."},
    {"p": "先……，然后……", "e": "先…然后… links two actions in order: 'first ..., then ...'. Each part is a full verb phrase, e.g. 先吃饭，然后看书.", "x": "我先借了两本别的书，然后把名字写在借书卡上。 — I first borrowed two other books, then wrote my name on the library card."},
    {"p": "……才 + verb", "e": "才 marks that something happens later than hoped or expected — 'not until'. It goes right before the verb, e.g. 他十点才起床.", "x": "那本书下星期一才会还回来。 — The book won't be returned until next Monday."}
